        <h3>RCIA - Rite of Christian Initiation of Adults</h3>
        <p>The Rite of Christian Initiation of Adults introduces these interested in joining the in joining the Catholic Church or in completing the Sacraments of Initiation in the church to our faith community and our Catholic belieffs.  The RCIA program consists of the steps and perios that make up the full and paradigmatic form of Christian initiation. All are welcome to inquire about and attend RCIA as you discern with the guidance of the Holy Spirit your faith journey.</p>
        <h3>Scripture Class/Bible Study</h3>
        <p>Incarnation–St. James parish offers Bible-study class twice a week, once in the afternoon and once in the evening.  We use the “Great Adventure: A Journey through the Bible” series by author Jeff Cavins.  The series consists of a Scripture workbook and DVDs on which Cavins teaches the Scripture study topic for that week.  This year we are looking forward to studying Corinthians and the Prophets.  Please join the Scripture study group if you are interested in deepening your knowledge of sacred Scripture and sharing your faith.</p>
        <h3>Centering Prayer Group</h3>
        <p>Our Incarnation–St. James Centering Prayer Group meets on Tuesday evenings, twice a month.  Centering prayer opens our mind and heart—our whole being—to God, the Ultimate Mystery, beyond thoughts, words and emotions.  By sitting quietly, consenting to God’s presence and action within us and focusing on a sacred word for 20 minutes, you will be centering.</p>
        <h3>Bereavement Group</h3>
        <p>Our Incarnation–St. James Bereavement Group welcomes those who have lost a loved one through death and feel the need for support and healing.  We meet one Saturday a month. Please consider joining the bereavement group for support, solace and healing as you grieve the loss of your loved one</p>
        <h3>Women of Joy</h3>
        <p>The Incarnation–St.  James Women of Joy come together with the vision of “women bringing women closer to God.”  Our group meets one Saturday a month. Our mission is living joyfully, sharing our faith journey, nurturing one another and growing together in the knowledge of God through prayer and Scripture.  We begin with breakfast (everyone brings a breakfast item to share), followed by faith sharing and a presentation on prayer or sacred Scripture or some other topic of interest to the group.</p>
